  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Human-in-the-Loop and Interrupts\n",
    "\n",
    "Production agents often need a **human gate** before irreversible actions: executing tools, sending emails, charging cards, or deploying code. LangGraph **interrupts** pause a compiled graph **before or after named nodes**, persist state via a **checkpointer**, and let you **inspect**, **edit**, or **reject** work before **resuming**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook covers **`interrupt_before`** / **`interrupt_after`** on **`compile()`**, **`MemorySaver`** requirements, **`get_state`** / **`update_state`**, the **`Command(resume=...)`** pattern (LangGraph 0.2+/1.x), tool-approval workflows, editing tool args, HITL ReAct agents, streaming while paused, and production timeouts with audit logs.\n",
    "\n",
    "Prerequisites: **06. Agent Loops and the ReAct Pattern**, **07. Tool Nodes and Tool Execution**, **08. Checkpointing and Thread Persistence**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "OPENAI_API_KEY = \"sk-proj-placeholder-replace-with-your-real-key\"\n",
    "\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from datetime import datetime, timezone\n",
    "from typing import Annotated, Literal\n",
    "from typing_extensions import TypedDict\n",
    "\n",
    "import langchain_core\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    import langgraph\n",
    "    print(\"langgraph:\", langgraph.__version__)\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    print(\"langgraph: pip install langgraph\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"langchain-core:\", langchain_core.__version__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Why Human-in-the-Loop?\n",
    "\n",
    "Agents can propose **dangerous or wrong tool calls**. A human reviewer (or policy engine) should approve, edit, or reject before execution.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "User question\n",
    "     │\n",
    "     ▼\n",
    "┌─────────┐   tool_calls    ┌──────────────┐   approve    ┌─────────┐\n",
    "│  model  │ ──────────────► │  INTERRUPT   │ ───────────► │  tools  │\n",
    "└─────────┘                 │  (human UI)  │              └────┬────┘\n",
    "                            │  edit/reject │                   │\n",
    "                            └──────────────┘                   ▼\n",
    "                                                          model → END\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "| Without HITL | With LangGraph interrupts |\n",
    "|--------------|---------------------------|\n",
    "| Custom HTTP pause + session store | Built-in checkpoint + resume |\n",
    "| Race on concurrent resumes | Thread-scoped `thread_id` |\n",
    "| Hard to edit agent state mid-flight | `update_state` patches checkpoint |\n",
    "| Opaque where execution stopped | `get_state().next` shows pending nodes |\n",
    "\n",
    "Notebook **05** previewed `interrupt_before=[\"generate\"]`. Here we implement the full approval loop around **tools** (**06**, **07**)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. Interrupt API on `compile()`\n",
    "\n",
    "Static interrupts are declared at **compile time** (**03**):\n",
    "\n",
    "| Parameter | Pauses |\n",
    "|-----------|--------|\n",
    "| **`interrupt_before=[\"tools\"]`** | After upstream nodes finish, **before** `tools` runs |\n",
    "| **`interrupt_after=[\"model\"]`** | **After** `model` completes, before the router picks next |\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "interrupt_before=[\"tools\"]:\n",
    "\n",
    "  START → model ──► ⏸ PAUSE ──► tools → model → END\n",
    "                         ▲\n",
    "                         └── human reviews tool_calls here\n",
    "\n",
    "interrupt_after=[\"model\"]:\n",
    "\n",
    "  START → model ──► ⏸ PAUSE ──► (router decides) → tools or END\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Node names must match** `add_node` labels exactly — they appear in traces, stream events, and interrupt configs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 3. Checkpointer Required\n",
    "\n",
    "Interrupts **require** a checkpointer — the graph must **persist** partial state between `invoke` calls. Without one, there is nothing to resume.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Backend | Use case |\n",
    "|---------|----------|\n",
    "| **`MemorySaver`** | Notebooks, unit tests (**08**) |\n",
    "| **`SqliteSaver` / Postgres** | Production multi-worker APIs (**16**) |\n",
    "\n",
    "Every resume call must pass the same **`configurable.thread_id`** as the original run."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import MemorySaver\n",
    "from langgraph.graph import END, START, StateGraph\n",
    "from langgraph.types import Command\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class CounterState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    count: int\n",
    "    log: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def node_a(state: CounterState) -> dict:\n",
    "    return {\"count\": state.get(\"count\", 0) + 1, \"log\": [\"a\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def node_b(state: CounterState) -> dict:\n",
    "    return {\"count\": state[\"count\"] + 10, \"log\": [\"b\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_counter_graph(interrupt_before: list[str] | None = None):\n",
    "    builder = StateGraph(CounterState)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"a\", node_a)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"b\", node_b)\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(START, \"a\")\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(\"a\", \"b\")\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(\"b\", END)\n",
    "    return builder.compile(\n",
    "        checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "        interrupt_before=interrupt_before or [],\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "counter_graph = build_counter_graph(interrupt_before=[\"b\"])\n",
    "thread_config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"counter-demo-1\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "counter_graph.invoke({\"count\": 0, \"log\": []}, thread_config)\n",
    "snapshot = counter_graph.get_state(thread_config)\n",
    "print(\"after first invoke:\")\n",
    "print(\"  values:\", snapshot.values)\n",
    "print(\"  next:\", snapshot.next)\n",
    "\n",
    "final = counter_graph.invoke(Command(resume=True), thread_config)\n",
    "print(\"after resume:\", final)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**`next=('b',)`** means node `b` is scheduled but paused. **`count=1`** — `a` ran; `b` has not. **`Command(resume=True)`** continues execution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. `interrupt_after` — Pause After a Node\n",
    "\n",
    "Use **`interrupt_after`** when the human needs to see **node output** before routing decides the next step:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "after_graph = build_counter_graph()  # no interrupt_before\n",
    "after_builder = StateGraph(CounterState)\n",
    "after_builder.add_node(\"a\", node_a)\n",
    "after_builder.add_node(\"b\", node_b)\n",
    "after_builder.add_edge(START, \"a\")\n",
    "after_builder.add_edge(\"a\", \"b\")\n",
    "after_builder.add_edge(\"b\", END)\n",
    "after_graph = after_builder.compile(\n",
    "    checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "    interrupt_after=[\"a\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "cfg2 = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"counter-after-1\"}}\n",
    "after_graph.invoke({\"count\": 0, \"log\": []}, cfg2)\n",
    "snap2 = after_graph.get_state(cfg2)\n",
    "print(\"interrupt_after a → values:\", snap2.values, \"next:\", snap2.next)\n",
    "\n",
    "done = after_graph.invoke(Command(resume=True), cfg2)\n",
    "print(\"resumed:\", done)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With **`interrupt_after=[\"a\"]`**, `a` completes (`count=1`, `log=['a']`) and execution pauses **before** `b` is entered — same `next` as `interrupt_before=[\"b\"]`, but the semantic hook differs for auditing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. `get_state` — Inspect While Paused\n",
    "\n",
    "Your API/UI calls **`graph.get_state(config)`** to render the approval screen. Key fields on the snapshot:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cfg3 = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"inspect-demo\"}}\n",
    "counter_graph.invoke({\"count\": 0, \"log\": []}, cfg3)\n",
    "snap = counter_graph.get_state(cfg3)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"values:\", snap.values)\n",
    "print(\"next nodes:\", snap.next)\n",
    "print(\"config:\", snap.config.get(\"configurable\"))\n",
    "print(\"created_at:\", getattr(snap, \"created_at\", \"n/a\"))\n",
    "print(\"tasks:\", len(snap.tasks) if snap.tasks else 0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In a FastAPI handler (**16**), return `snapshot.values` + `snapshot.next` to the frontend. The client shows pending tool calls and posts approve/reject to a resume endpoint."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 6. `update_state` — Edit Before Resume\n",
    "\n",
    "Humans may **correct tool arguments** or inject feedback without re-running the model. **`update_state`** writes a checkpoint patch **while paused**:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class DraftState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    question: str\n",
    "    draft: str\n",
    "    approved: bool\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def propose_draft(state: DraftState) -> dict:\n",
    "    return {\"draft\": f\"DRAFT answer for: {state['question']}\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def publish_draft(state: DraftState) -> dict:\n",
    "    return {\"approved\": True}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "draft_builder = StateGraph(DraftState)\n",
    "draft_builder.add_node(\"propose\", propose_draft)\n",
    "draft_builder.add_node(\"publish\", publish_draft)\n",
    "draft_builder.add_edge(START, \"propose\")\n",
    "draft_builder.add_edge(\"propose\", \"publish\")\n",
    "draft_builder.add_edge(\"publish\", END)\n",
    "\n",
    "draft_graph = draft_builder.compile(\n",
    "    checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "    interrupt_before=[\"publish\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "cfg4 = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"draft-edit-1\"}}\n",
    "draft_graph.invoke({\"question\": \"JWT header?\", \"draft\": \"\", \"approved\": False}, cfg4)\n",
    "\n",
    "before = draft_graph.get_state(cfg4).values\n",
    "print(\"before edit:\", before[\"draft\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "draft_graph.update_state(\n",
    "    cfg4,\n",
    "    {\"draft\": \"Send Authorization: Bearer <token> per [c3].\"},\n",
    "    as_node=\"propose\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "edited = draft_graph.get_state(cfg4).values\n",
    "print(\"after edit:\", edited[\"draft\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "final_draft = draft_graph.invoke(Command(resume=True), cfg4)\n",
    "print(\"published:\", final_draft)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**`as_node`** records which node produced the edit — useful for audit trails. For message-based agents, patch the last **`AIMessage`** (tool args) the same way."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 7. `Command(resume=...)` — Resume Pattern\n",
    "\n",
    "LangGraph 0.2+/1.x uses **`Command`** from **`langgraph.types`** to resume interrupted runs. The resume payload can carry human decisions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class ApprovalState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    action: str\n",
    "    decision: str\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def plan_action(state: ApprovalState) -> dict:\n",
    "    return {\"action\": \"delete_note n99\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def execute_action(state: ApprovalState) -> dict:\n",
    "    "    return {\"decision\": f\"executed: {state['action']}\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "approval_builder = StateGraph(ApprovalState)\n",
    "approval_builder.add_node(\"plan\", plan_action)\n",
    "approval_builder.add_node(\"execute\", execute_action)\n",
    "approval_builder.add_edge(START, \"plan\")\n",
    "approval_builder.add_edge(\"plan\", \"execute\")\n",
    "approval_builder.add_edge(\"execute\", END)\n",
    "\n",
    "approval_graph = approval_builder.compile(\n",
    "    checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "    interrupt_before=[\"execute\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "cfg5 = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"approval-1\"}}\n",
    "approval_graph.invoke({\"action\": \"\", \"decision\": \"\"}, cfg5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Human rejects — resume with a decision payload\n",
    "rejected = approval_graph.invoke(Command(resume=\"reject\"), cfg5)\n",
    "print(\"reject path:\", rejected)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fresh thread — approve\n",
    "cfg6 = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"approval-2\"}}\n",
    "approval_graph.invoke({\"action\": \"\", \"decision\": \"\"}, cfg6)\n",
    "approved = approval_graph.invoke(Command(resume=\"approve\"), cfg6)\n",
    "print(\"approve path:\", approved)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Nodes can read **`interrupt()`** return values for dynamic gates (**16**). Static **`interrupt_before`** + **`Command(resume=...)`** covers most HITL tool-approval UIs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 8. Notes API Corpus and Tools\n",
    "\n",
    "Reuse **n1–n4** notes and **c1–c5** chunks from **06** / **01. LangChain/12**:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_core.messages import AIMessage, HumanMessage, ToolMessage\n",
    "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
    "from langgraph.graph.message import add_messages\n",
    "\n",
    "NOTES = {\n",
    "    \"n1\": \"The Notes API is built with FastAPI. Routes live under /notes.\",\n",
    "    \"n2\": \"Run alembic upgrade head after pulling database migrations.\",\n",
    "    \"n3\": \"JWT bearer tokens use Authorization: Bearer header.\",\n",
    "    \"n4\": \"Pytest fixtures for DB setup belong in conftest.py.\",\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "DOC_CHUNKS = [\n",
    "    {\"id\": \"c1\", \"text\": NOTES[\"n1\"]},\n",
    "    {\"id\": \"c2\", \"text\": NOTES[\"n2\"]},\n",
    "    {\"id\": \"c3\", \"text\": NOTES[\"n3\"]},\n",
    "    {\"id\": \"c4\", \"text\": NOTES[\"n4\"]},\n",
    "    {\"id\": \"c5\", \"text\": \"Alembic autogenerate compares models to live schema and drafts revisions.\"},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def get_note(note_id: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Fetch a note by id (n1, n2, n3, n4).\"\"\"\n",
    "    return NOTES.get(note_id, f\"Unknown note id: {note_id}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def search_docs(query: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Keyword search over documentation chunks c1-c5.\"\"\"\n",
    "    tokens = set(query.lower().split())\n",
    "    hits = [f\"[{c['id']}] {c['text']}\" for c in DOC_CHUNKS if tokens & set(c[\"text\"].lower().split())]\n",
    "    return \"\\n\".join(hits) if hits else \"No matching chunks.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def delete_note(note_id: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"DESTRUCTIVE: delete a note by id. Requires human approval.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return f\"Deleted note {note_id}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "TOOLS = [get_note, search_docs, delete_note]\n",
    "TOOLS_BY_NAME = {t.name: t for t in TOOLS}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 9. Tool Approval Workflow (Fake Agent)\n",
    "\n",
    "Build a ReAct-shaped graph with **`interrupt_before=[\"tools\"]`**. The model proposes tool calls; execution waits for human approval:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class AgentState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    messages: Annotated[list, add_messages]\n",
    "    audit_log: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def fake_model(state: AgentState) -> dict:\n",
    "    last = state[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "    text = last.content.lower() if hasattr(last, \"content\") else \"\"\n",
    "    if any(isinstance(m, ToolMessage) for m in state[\"messages\"]):\n",
    "        ai = AIMessage(content=\"JWT uses Authorization: Bearer header [c3].\")\n",
    "    elif \"jwt\" in text:\n",
    "        ai = AIMessage(\n",
    "            content=\"\",\n",
    "            tool_calls=[{\n",
    "                \"name\": \"search_docs\",\n",
    "                \"args\": {\"query\": \"jwt bearer\"},\n",
    "                \"id\": \"call_search_1\",\n",
    "                \"type\": \"tool_call\",\n",
    "            }],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    elif \"delete\" in text:\n",
    "        ai = AIMessage(\n",
    "            content=\"\",\n",
    "            tool_calls=[{\n",
    "                \"name\": \"delete_note\",\n",
    "                \"args\": {\"note_id\": \"n3\"},\n",
    "                \"id\": \"call_delete_1\",\n",
    "                \"type\": \"tool_call\",\n",
    "            }],\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        ai = AIMessage(content=\"Ask about Notes API docs or note ids n1-n4.\")\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": [ai], \"audit_log\": [\"model_proposed\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def run_tools(state: AgentState) -> dict:\n",
    "    last = state[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "    if not isinstance(last, AIMessage) or not last.tool_calls:\n",
    "        return {}\n",
    "    tool_msgs = []\n",
    "    for tc in last.tool_calls:\n",
    "        tool = TOOLS_BY_NAME[tc[\"name\"]]\n",
    "        result = str(tool.invoke(tc[\"args\"]))\n",
    "        tool_msgs.append(ToolMessage(content=result, tool_call_id=tc[\"id\"]))\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": tool_msgs, \"audit_log\": [\"tools_executed\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def should_continue(state: AgentState):\n",
    "    last = state[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "    if isinstance(last, AIMessage) and last.tool_calls:\n",
    "        return \"tools\"\n",
    "    return END\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_hitl_agent():\n",
    "    builder = StateGraph(AgentState)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"model\", fake_model)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"tools\", run_tools)\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(START, \"model\")\n",
    "    builder.add_conditional_edges(\"model\", should_continue)\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(\"tools\", \"model\")\n",
    "    return builder.compile(\n",
    "        checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "        interrupt_before=[\"tools\"],\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "hitl_agent = build_hitl_agent()\n",
    "hitl_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"hitl-jwt-1\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "hitl_agent.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"JWT header format?\")], \"audit_log\": []}, hitl_cfg)\n",
    "paused = hitl_agent.get_state(hitl_cfg)\n",
    "pending_ai = paused.values[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "print(\"PAUSED — pending tool calls:\", pending_ai.tool_calls)\n",
    "print(\"next:\", paused.next)\n",
    "\n",
    "result = hitl_agent.invoke(Command(resume=\"approve\"), hitl_cfg)\n",
    "print(\"final message:\", result[\"messages\"][-1].content)\n",
    "print(\"audit:\", result[\"audit_log\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Trace: **`human → ai (tool_calls) → ⏸ → tools → ai (final)`**. The interrupt fires **after** the model node and router select `tools`, but **before** `tools` executes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 10. Reject or Edit Tool Args\n",
    "\n",
    "Three human decisions before resume:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "| Decision | Mechanism | Effect |\n",
    "|----------|-----------|--------|\n",
    "| **Approve** | `Command(resume=\"approve\")` | Run `tools` with current `tool_calls` |\n",
    "| **Edit args** | `update_state` → replace `AIMessage.tool_calls` | Human-corrected args execute |\n",
    "| **Reject** | `update_state` → strip `tool_calls`, add rejection text | Model sees rejection on next turn |\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "approve:  get_state → UI OK → Command(resume=True)\n",
    "edit:     get_state → UI edits args → update_state → Command(resume=True)\n",
    "reject:   get_state → update_state (no tool_calls) → Command(resume=True) OR route to END\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def show_pending_tool_calls(graph, config):\n",
    "    snap = graph.get_state(config)\n",
    "    last = snap.values[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "    if isinstance(last, AIMessage) and last.tool_calls:\n",
    "        return last.tool_calls\n",
    "    return []\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Edit args: change delete target from n3 to n1 ---\n",
    "edit_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"hitl-edit-1\"}}\n",
    "hitl_agent.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"delete note n3 please\")], \"audit_log\": []}, edit_cfg)\n",
    "print(\"pending:\", show_pending_tool_calls(hitl_agent, edit_cfg))\n",
    "\n",
    "snap = hitl_agent.get_state(edit_cfg)\n",
    "ai_msg = snap.values[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "edited_calls = [{**tc, \"args\": {\"note_id\": \"n1\"}} for tc in ai_msg.tool_calls]\n",
    "edited_ai = AIMessage(content=ai_msg.content, tool_calls=edited_calls, id=ai_msg.id)\n",
    "\n",
    "hitl_agent.update_state(edit_cfg, {\"messages\": [edited_ai]}, as_node=\"model\")\n",
    "print(\"edited pending:\", show_pending_tool_calls(hitl_agent, edit_cfg))\n",
    "\n",
    "edited_result = hitl_agent.invoke(Command(resume=\"approve\"), edit_cfg)\n",
    "tool_result = [m for m in edited_result[\"messages\"] if isinstance(m, ToolMessage)][-1]\n",
    "print(\"tool result:\", tool_result.content)\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Reject: strip tool_calls, inject human feedback ---\n",
    "reject_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"hitl-reject-1\"}}\n",
    "hitl_agent.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"delete note n3\")], \"audit_log\": []}, reject_cfg)\n",
    "\n",
    "snap_r = hitl_agent.get_state(reject_cfg)\n",
    "ai_r = snap_r.values[\"messages\"][-1]\n",
    "rejection = AIMessage(\n",
    "    content=\"Human rejected delete_note — destructive actions are not allowed.\",\n",
    "    id=ai_r.id,\n",
    ")\n",
    "hitl_agent.update_state(reject_cfg, {\"messages\": [rejection], \"audit_log\": [\"human_rejected\"]}, as_node=\"model\")\n",
    "print(\"rejection logged — next:\", hitl_agent.get_state(reject_cfg).next)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Production UIs render **`tool_calls`** as editable JSON forms. **`delete_note`** is a stand-in for any side-effecting tool (**07**, **14**)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 11. HITL with Live ReAct Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "Swap the fake model for a real LLM — same interrupt policy:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n",
    "\n",
    "llm = ChatOpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY, temperature=0)\n",
    "llm_with_tools = llm.bind_tools(TOOLS)\n",
    "SYSTEM = \"You are a Notes API assistant. Use search_docs and get_note. Never call delete_note unless the user explicitly requests deletion.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def call_model(state: AgentState) -> dict:\n",
    "    messages = [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM}] + state[\"messages\"]\n",
    "    response = llm_with_tools.invoke(messages)\n",
    "    return {\"messages\": [response], \"audit_log\": [\"model_live\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_live_hitl_agent():\n",
    "    builder = StateGraph(AgentState)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"model\", call_model)\n",
    "    builder.add_node(\"tools\", run_tools)\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(START, \"model\")\n",
    "    builder.add_conditional_edges(\"model\", should_continue)\n",
    "    builder.add_edge(\"tools\", \"model\")\n",
    "    return builder.compile(\n",
    "        checkpointer=MemorySaver(),\n",
    "        interrupt_before=[\"tools\"],\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "live_hitl = build_live_hitl_agent()\n",
    "live_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"live-hitl-1\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "live_hitl.invoke(\n",
    "    {\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"What note id covers JWT? Use tools.\")], \"audit_log\": []},\n",
    "    live_cfg,\n",
    ")\n",
    "live_snap = live_hitl.get_state(live_cfg)\n",
    "print(\"live pending:\", live_snap.next)\n",
    "print(\"tool_calls:\", live_snap.values[\"messages\"][-1].tool_calls)\n",
    "\n",
    "live_final = live_hitl.invoke(Command(resume=\"approve\"), live_cfg)\n",
    "print(\"live answer:\", live_final[\"messages\"][-1].content[:200])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Same topology as **`create_agent`** (**01. LangChain/13**) plus **`interrupt_before=[\"tools\"]`** — you keep full control over the approval UI."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 12. Streaming While Interrupted\n",
    "\n",
    "Stream node updates on the initial run and again on resume (**13**):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "stream_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"hitl-stream-1\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== initial stream (stops at interrupt) ===\")\n",
    "for update in hitl_agent.stream(\n",
    "    {\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"JWT bearer token?\")], \"audit_log\": []},\n",
    "    stream_cfg,\n",
    "    stream_mode=\"updates\",\n",
    "):\n",
    "    print(update)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\npaused next:\", hitl_agent.get_state(stream_cfg).next)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== resume stream ===\")\n",
    "for update in hitl_agent.stream(Command(resume=\"approve\"), stream_cfg, stream_mode=\"updates\"):\n",
    "    print(update)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First stream emits **`model`** update then stops. Resume stream emits **`tools`** then **`model`**. Use **`stream_mode=\"values\"`** for full state snapshots in SSE endpoints."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 13. Production — Timeout and Audit Log\n",
    "\n",
    "Wrap HITL in service-layer policies (**16**):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "HITL_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 300  # 5 minutes\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def utc_now() -> str:\n",
    "    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def log_audit(state: dict, event: str, detail: str) -> list[str]:\n",
    "    entry = json.dumps({\"ts\": utc_now(), \"event\": event, \"detail\": detail})\n",
    "    return state.get(\"audit_log\", []) + [entry]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def resume_with_policy(graph, config: dict, decision: Literal[\"approve\", \"reject\"], *, actor: str = \"human\"):\n",
    "    snap = graph.get_state(config)\n",
    "    if not snap.next:\n",
    "        return {\"status\": \"not_paused\", \"state\": snap.values}\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Timeout check — compare against checkpoint timestamp in production DB\n",
    "    created = getattr(snap, \"created_at\", None)\n",
    "    if created:\n",
    "        age = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - created).total_seconds()\n",
    "        if age > HITL_TIMEOUT_SECONDS:\n",
    "            graph.update_state(\n",
    "                config,\n",
    "                {\"audit_log\": [json.dumps({\"ts\": utc_now(), \"event\": \"timeout\", \"actor\": actor})]},\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            return {\"status\": \"expired\", \"age_seconds\": age}\n",
    "\n",
    "    graph.update_state(\n",
    "        config,\n",
    "        {\"audit_log\": [json.dumps({\"ts\": utc_now(), \"event\": decision, \"actor\": actor, \"next\": list(snap.next)})]},\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    result = graph.invoke(Command(resume=decision), config)\n",
    "    return {\"status\": \"resumed\", \"decision\": decision, \"state\": result}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "prod_cfg = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"hitl-prod-1\"}}\n",
    "hitl_agent.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=\"JWT?\")], \"audit_log\": []}, prod_cfg)\n",
    "outcome = resume_with_policy(hitl_agent, prod_cfg, \"approve\", actor=\"reviewer@example.com\")\n",
    "print(\"status:\", outcome[\"status\"])\n",
    "print(\"audit tail:\", outcome[\"state\"][\"audit_log\"][-2:])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Store **`audit_log`** in Postgres alongside checkpoints. Expire stale interrupts with a cron job or on the next `get_state` call. Never resume without authenticating the **`actor`**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 14. Interrupt Placement in Larger Graphs\n",
    "\n",
    "From **05**, place interrupts on sensitive nodes in the full documentation graph:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "```\n",
    "guard → classify → retrieve → grade → ⏸ generate → END\n",
    "                                         ▲\n",
    "                              interrupt_before=[\"generate\"]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "| Interrupt point | Review what |\n",
    "|-----------------|-------------|\n",
    "| **`generate`** | Draft answer before user sees it |\n",
    "| **`tools`** | Tool calls before side effects |\n",
    "| **`publish`** | Final outbound payload |\n",
    "\n",
    "Combine with subgraphs (**10**) to isolate the agent loop behind a single interrupt boundary."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 15. Design Guidelines\n",
    "\n",
    "| Guideline | Rationale |\n",
    "|-----------|----------|\n",
    "| **Interrupt before side effects** | `tools`, `publish`, `send_email` — not `model` unless reviewing drafts |\n",
    "| **Stable `thread_id` per conversation** | Resume must target the same checkpoint |\n",
    "| **Compile once with interrupt policy** | Policy is baked into `CompiledStateGraph` |\n",
    "| **Audit every decision** | Compliance and debugging |\n",
    "| **Timeout abandoned interrupts** | Prevent stale approvals |\n",
    "| **Authenticate resume endpoints** | Anyone with `thread_id` must not resume |\n",
    "| **Show `tool_calls` as structured UI** | Reduce arg-edit errors |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 16. Common Mistakes\n",
    "\n",
    "| Mistake | Consequence | Fix |\n",
    "|---------|-------------|-----|\n",
    "| No checkpointer | Interrupt silently ignored or error | `compile(checkpointer=MemorySaver())` |\n",
    "| Wrong node name in interrupt list | Never pauses | Match `add_node` names exactly |\n",
    "| New `thread_id` on resume | Starts fresh run | Reuse original config |\n",
    "| Resume without checking `next` | No-op or error | `if snap.next:` before resume |\n",
    "| Edit messages without `as_node` | Confusing audit trail | Pass `as_node=\"model\"` |\n",
    "| Interrupt on every node | UX fatigue | Only irreversible steps |\n",
    "| No timeout on pending approvals | Stale state accumulates | Expire + notify |\n",
    "| Recompile per request | Slow; wrong interrupt policy | Build graph at startup |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 17. Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "**`interrupt_before`** / **`interrupt_after`** on **`compile()`** pause execution at named nodes. A **checkpointer** (`MemorySaver` in dev, Postgres in prod) persists state between calls. Inspect with **`get_state`**, patch with **`update_state`**, and continue with **`Command(resume=...)`**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key takeaways:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **HITL** gates irreversible **tool** execution in the ReAct loop (**06**, **07**).\n",
    "- Humans can **approve**, **edit tool args**, or **reject** via `update_state`.\n",
    "- **`get_state().next`** tells you which node is waiting.\n",
    "- **Streaming** works across interrupt boundaries (**13**).\n",
    "- **Audit logs** and **timeouts** are required for production (**16**).\n",
    "\n",
    "Demonstrations built counter interrupts, draft editing, fake and live tool-approval agents, arg editing, rejection flows, streaming, and audit-wrapped resume.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next: **10. Subgraphs and Nested Workflows** — embed compiled graphs as nodes inside larger routers from **05**."
   ]
  }
